on American Public Media's Performance Today on The Art of Practicing    Incoming Freshmen Recommended Materials    Professor Haas and MA candidate Sean Statser receive glowing review from NY Times       Selected Events       Summer Percussion Broadway Seminar / Summit       Featured Students       Read about our current students              Studies in percussion performance at NYU provide aspiring students advanced performance training combined with the finest related academic and music courses. The B.M. and M.M. programs in music performance attract accomplished musicians interested in intensive training for careers in music performance. In addition to traditional studies in music theory and history, percussion students:       study with renowned faculty through private lessons    participate in ensembles and chamber music, symphony and repertory orchestras, and percussion ensemble    prepare for solo recital performances    attend master classes with New York City's leading percussion players       The Ph.D. in music performance is designed for successful performing artists who wish to develop an area of specialization through music research in preparation for university teaching and scholarly publication.    The Department of Music and Performing Arts offers a warm, collegial atmosphere where percussion performers enjoy the support of all faculty and their peers. Our reputation, faculty, and location provide students with a unique opportunity to develop as performers and to make the contacts necessary to launch a professional career.    The overall goal of the NYU Percussion Studies program is to provide a rewarding and fulfilling musical experience while simultaneously preparing each student to be a serious competitor in the multi-faceted music industry. The percussion studio operates in an atmosphere of cooperation and shared responsibility. Its members cultivate a spirit of mutual respect: a vital ingredient for organized, prepared, and professional training and performance. Ultimately, our goal is to serve music at the highest standard.    Scholarships are available and awarded for musical and academic excellence.    The Department's acclaimed programs of study in Music Business (B.M., M.A.), Music Technology (B.M., M.M., Ph.D.), Jazz (B.M., M.M., Ph.D.), Music Composition (B.M., M.M., Ph.D.), and Music Education (B.M., M.A., Ph.D.) provide a rich and valuable array of elective courses for music performance majors that prepare them for an ever-changing music industry and musical climate. Our undergraduate and graduate students benefit from the extraordinary opportunities available through the diverse offerings of a major university in the cultural capital of the world, New York City.
